{
  "texts": [
    "• Data-level strategies, also known as external strategies, focus on modifying the dataset to rebalance the class distribution.",
    "Techniques such as oversampling, undersampling,",
    "and hybrid methods are employed.",
    "Oversampling methods generate synthetic examples or replicate existing instances of the minority class to augment its representation.",
    "Conversely, undersampling methods reduce the number of examples from the majority class to achieve a more balanced dataset."
  ]
}